Text Count: 2,583, reading time approximately 4.5 minutes

Introduction: with the spread of the epidemic, confirmed and suspected patients increased, whether patients can obtain a bed is of great concern. At present, the disaster areas through new construction, reconstruction, expansion of the form of additional beds to ensure that "should live, should receive. ".

Author | Caijing No. 1 Chen Yikan

The number of cases of COVID-19 pneumonia is increasing. What is the treatment capacity? Can Medical Supplies, beds, medical staff, etc. Keep up?

As of 2400 hours on February 1, a total of 14,380 cases of COVID-19 pneumonia (hereinafter referred to as "new crown pneumonia") had been reported in 31 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities directly under the Central Government) and Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps, according to the National Health Commission.

Nationwide, there were 2,590 new confirmed cases a day, of which 1,921 were in Hubei Province.

As of 24:00 on February 1, Wuhan (4,109 cases) , Huanggang (1,002 cases) , Xiaogan (749 cases) , Xiangyang (441 cases) and Suizhou (384 cases) were among the top five confirmed cases in China, all in Hubei Province.

In addition, more than 300 cases have been confirmed in Yichang, Jingzhou, Jingmen, Ezhou, Huangshi, Shiyan, Xianning and Wenzhou, Zhejiang.

February 2, according to the Wuhan City Prevention and Control Command requirements, new pneumonia confirmed patients centralized treatment, suspected patients centralized isolation, fever patients, close contacts centralized isolation observation. According to this request, the epidemic area, has this kind of admission capacity?

The people are most concerned about, the new outbreak of pneumonia focus on the place "can be admitted to the upper house. ". First Finance reporter collated the number of confirmed cases of new pneumonia in hospitals in top 5 cities of capacity. At present, all parts of Hubei are coordinating the deployment of medical resources, vacating as many beds as possible, to speed up the progress of the renovation of new hospitals and wards.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Nearly 7,000 beds have been used in Wuhan, and the new hospital will be opened

As the outbreak area of NCP and the largest disaster area, the situation of the ward in the Designated Hospital of NCP in Wuhan has attracted the most attention.

As of 2400 hours on February 1,4109 cases of new coronary pneumonia had been confirmed in Wuhan. Among them, 892 new cases were confirmed in Wuhan on January 27, the daily increase of more than 300 cases was maintained in the following three days, 576 cases were added on January 31, and 894 cases were added on February 1.

As of 23:00 on Feb. 1, there were 6,754 open beds in three batches of 23 designated hospitals for new pneumonia in Wuhan, with 6,808 beds in use and 175 empty beds, according to the Wuhan Municipal Health and Health Commission. Among them, there are cases in some hospitals where the number of beds already used is greater than the number of beds open. This is because some hospitals, in accordance with the requirement of "collecting all available beds" , try their best to arrange additional beds for more suspected patients, resulting in open beds not fully equal to the number of beds already used plus the number of empty beds. Moreover, the capacity of empty beds will also be affected by dynamic changes.

First Financial reporter learned that Wuhan New Crown Pneumonia beds will continue to increase.

In order to solve the problem of hospitalization, Wuhan urgently started construction of two hospitals, namely the Fire God Mountain Hospital and the Thunder God Mountain Hospital, the two hospitals together plan is 2,000 ~ 2,300 beds.

On the morning of February 2, the Mayor of Wuhan, Zhou Xianwang, and the deputy commander of the Joint Logistics Support Force, Bai Zhongbin, signed an exchange document at the Huoshenshan Hospital, marking the official delivery of the hospital to medical workers of the People's Army. The hospital mainly treats and treats the patients who have been diagnosed, and sets up 1,000 beds. It also sets up intensive care unit, Intensive Care Unit, General Unit, and auxiliary departments for infection control, examination, special diagnosis and radiation diagnosis. The army selected 1,400 medical personnel to undertake the medical treatment of the hospital from February 3. Thor Hill Hospital will be officially delivered on February 5.

In addition, the Under Secretary of the medical and Health Administration Bureau of the State Health Commission, Jiao Yahui, said on January 28 that the fourth batch of designated hospitals in Wuhan had been requisitioned, and the new hospital area of the Huazhong University of Science and Technology Tongji Hospital had been requisitioned in an emergency, it also includes 14 hospitals, including the Eastern District of the People's Hospital of Wuhan University, that have been able to vacate about 6,000 beds, all of which together amount to more than 10,000, and can accommodate current suspected and confirmed cases, including fever, pending investigation.

Jiao Yahui said it was not enough to have only beds. Nearly 6,000 medical staff were urgently deployed across the country, and when these beds were opened, they could all be put into the medical treatment of patients.

In addition to the local medical resources in Wuhan, according to statistics from the Hubei Provincial Headquarters for the prevention and control of new coronavirus pneumonia, as of 2400 hours on January 28, twenty-six provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities, including Beijing, Shanghai, Hunan and Sichuan, as well as three military hospitals have organized a total of 52 medical teams with 6,097 personnel to reinforce Hubei.

Some of the city and county beds in Huanggang are under strain

The outbreak in Huanggang, next to Wuhan, is also severe and is likely to increase significantly in the future.

On February 1,276 new cases of pneumonia were reported in Huanggang. As of 2400 hours on February 1,1,002 new cases had been reported in Huanggang, exceeding 1,000 cases. Qiu Lixin, Huanggang's mayor, said the more than 1,000 suspected cases in Huanggang would soon be detected on February 1 and 2, with a large proportion likely to be confirmed.

As of 2400 hours on 31 January, 695 cases had been hospitalized in designated hospitals in Huanggang, with a cumulative total of 6,306 close contacts tracked and 5,695 under medical observation.

According to official figures, Huanggang's new crown pneumonia designated hospitals are 29, with 4,200 beds. On January 24, Huanggang decided to convert the Dabie Mountains medical centre into a 1,000-bed intensive care hospital for three days. The hospital is already taking patients.

In the area of health-care workers, Huanggang has established a team of health-care workers with 2,901 doctors and 4,836 nurses working in the four specialties of respiratory, endocardial, infectious and severe diseases. More than 10,000 medical personnel were trained in two batches in disease diagnosis, critical care, personal protection and hospital sense prevention and control.

In addition, the CPC Hubei Provincial Committee and the provincial government sent guidance teams to Huanggang, and Hunan and Shandong sent four medical teams and a total of 540 people to support Huanggang to help develop treatment plans and actively treat infected patients.

On January 31, Ms Qiu said that Huanggang's medical capacity was still inadequate. Despite the gradual improvement in admission capacity, some counties and cities are facing the risk of cross-infection due to tight beds, inadequate medical care in rural areas, and inadequate classification and zoning of designated medical institutions.

In response, Huanggang will step up the construction and expropriation of hospitals to ensure that "all should be done, all should be collected" . Rational allocation of fixed-point medical institutions to achieve classification, classification and management.

Xiaogan and Xiangyang have both built "Little Tangshan" hospitals

Xiaogan epidemic situation is also more serious, as of February 1,24 hours, Xiaogan confirmed the number of 749 cases, ranking the third in the country, in addition to the cumulative tracking of close contacts of 5428 people, 5,066 people are still under medical observation.

According to Xiaogan city government data, the city has so far announced 31 new crown pneumonia fever clinics, identified 9 designated medical treatment institutions, set up isolation treatment areas in 9 Xiaogan City districts 3, each county and city 1, set up medical observation points 10.

In addition, the Xiaogan Command has commandeered a medical institution as a standby hospital, which will be opened in due course according to the progress of the epidemic and medical needs.

As of January 31, Xiaogan and the Yingcheng, Yunmeng County and Dawu County, Hubei under its jurisdiction have set up four "Xiaotangshan" model hospitals, with 990 beds, by expropriating existing hospitals; the Anlu Infectious Disease Hospital is in the process of being Split Second, it is expected to be put into use on February 5, with 500 beds, Xiaonan District Xihe, Xinhua, Dawu County, Sanli Town, a small "Xiaotangshan" disease area.

Control of the Xiangyang epidemic is not optimistic. As of February 1,441 cases had been confirmed, bringing the cumulative total of suspected cases to 547, all of whom were being treated under isolation in designated medical institutions, and 3,446 close contacts were tracked, with 88 people released from medical observation on the same day, according to the Xiangyang Health Commission, under medical observation. 3,092.

The number of fever clinics and sentinel clinics in Xiangyang has increased to 73 and 14 respectively. In addition, in order to relieve the pressure on medical institutions for the treatment of patients with NCP, Xiangyang has built an independent hospital for the treatment of epidemic patients  The Dongjin Hospital area of the Central Hospital of Xiangyang, which will initially provide 500 beds (single rooms) on February 1.

As of 2400 hours on February 1, there were 384 confirmed cases in Suizhou and 342 suspected cases in the city, according to Suizhou Health Commission. Five medical institutions for targeted treatment and 12 medical institutions for fever outpatient treatment have been set up in the city.

On February 1, the conference on the advancement of the prevention and control of the new crown pneumonia epidemic in Suizhou stressed that Suizhou should strengthen the construction of medical infrastructure, speed up the reserve of hospitals, and do a good job in the reconstruction of hospitals in accordance with the requirement of preparedness for emergencies, suspected Cases of mandatory isolation, admission, critical patients must meet the "three areas two channels" requirements.

(contributed by intern Manlin Zhang)
